    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="51"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                <head>51. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName> to
                    Egyptian President <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> and Israeli
                    Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d51fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Country File, Box 53, Middle East:
                        Camp David President’s Working Papers, 9/10–27/78. No classification
                        marking. The handwritten letter was found attached to a September 15 note by
                            <persName corresp="#p_CSS_1">Clough</persName> indicating that original
                        copies of the letter were hand delivered to <persName corresp="#p_SA_1"
                            >Sadat</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName> by
                            <persName corresp="#p_MW_1">Mondale</persName>. (Ibid.) In his personal
                        diary, <persName corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName> wrote that the text of
                        the letter was agreed at a meeting of the <gloss target="#t_US_1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> delegation in Aspen Lodge on the morning of September 15
                        and that both <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName> accepted the message. (<hi
                            rend="italic">White House Diary,</hi> p. 236) According to the
                        President’s Daily Diary, this meeting, involving <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MW_1"
                            >Mondale</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_JH_1">Jordan</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BH_2"
                            >Brown</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_PJ_1">Powell</persName>,
                        took place from 7:51 a.m. to 9:55 a.m. (Carter Library, Presidential
                        Materials) <persName corresp="#p_MW_1">Mondale</persName> delivered the
                        letter to <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName> on the afternoon of September 15.
                        (See <ref target="#d28fn66">footnotes 66</ref> and <ref target="#d28fn68"
                            >68</ref>, <ref target="#d28">Document 28</ref>)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Camp David</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-09-15">September 15, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>To Pres. <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> &amp; P.M.
                            <persName corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName>: </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>We are approaching the final stage of our negotiations. With your approval, I
                    propose that today we receive your most constructive recommendations, that
                    tomorrow (Saturday) be devoted to drafting efforts, and that we conclude the
                    meeting at Camp David at some time during the following day. We will, at that
                    time, issue a common statement to the press, drafted together. Additionally, we
                    should agree not to make any further public statements prior to noon on Monday.
                    Please let me know if you object to any of these proposals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">J.C.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
